00026 /// \ingroup (enums)
00027 /// \brief
00028 /// The FdoComparisonOperations enumeration lists the comparison operations
00029 /// available.
00030 enum FdoComparisonOperations
00031 {
00032     /// Test to see if the left and right expressions are equal.
00033     FdoComparisonOperations_EqualTo,
00034 
00035     /// Test to see if the left and right expressions are not equal.
00036     FdoComparisonOperations_NotEqualTo,
00037 
00038     /// Test to see if the left expression is greater than the right expression.
00039     FdoComparisonOperations_GreaterThan,
00040 
00041     /// Test to see if the left expression is greater than or equal to the right expression.
00042     FdoComparisonOperations_GreaterThanOrEqualTo,
00043 
00044     /// Test to see if the left expression is less than the right expression.
00045     FdoComparisonOperations_LessThan,
00046 
00047     /// Test to see if the left expression is less than or equal to the right expression.
00048     FdoComparisonOperations_LessThanOrEqualTo,
00049 
00050     /// Test to see if the left expression matches the pattern specified by the
00051     /// right expression.  Wildcard characters supported in the pattern are:
00052     //
00053     /// %    Any string of zero or more characters
00054     /// _    Any single character
00055     /// []   Any single character within the specified range ([a-f]) or set 
00056     /// ([abcdef]).
00057     /// [^]  Any single character not within the specified range ([^a-f]) or 
00058     /// set ([^abcdef]).
00059     FdoComparisonOperations_Like
00060 };
00061 #endif
